# 🌀 SmartBalancer – Load Balancer with Consistent Hashing in Node.js

This is a simple demo project that simulates a **load balancer** using **consistent hashing** to distribute incoming HTTP requests across multiple backend servers.

## 🚀 Features

- 🔁 Consistent hashing ensures "sticky" routing (same user → same server).
- 📦 Lightweight setup with native `http`, `http-proxy`, and `hashring`.
- 🧪 Great for learning and prototyping scalable architectures.

---

## 🧱 Folder Structure
smart-balancer/
├── load-balancer.js # Load balancer with consistent hashing
├── server1.js # Backend server 1 (port 3001)
├── server2.js # Backend server 2 (port 3002)
├── server3.js # Backend server 3 (port 3003)
├── package.json
└── README.md

## 📦 Installation
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/smart-balancer.git
cd smart-balancer
npm install

▶️ Running the Project
In separate terminals, run:
node server1.js
node server2.js
node server3.js  each server listens on ports 3001, 3002, and 3003 respectively.

Start the Load Balancer
In a new terminal, run:
node load-balancer.js


Open your browser:
http://localhost:8000/user1
http://localhost:8000/user2
http://localhost:8000/user1
